     <subsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
        id="ID.0072"
        title="Sentences and Paragraphs"
        rolemaps-to="H3"
       >
      <section-number xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0073"
         rolemaps-to="Span"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>2.2.1
      </section-number>
      <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>Sentences and Paragraphs
     </subsection>
     <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0074"
        rolemaps-to="Part"
       >
      <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0075"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
         rolemaps-to="P"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>As any dedicated reader can clearly see, the Ideal of practical reason is a rep-resentation of, as far as I know, the things in themselves; as I have shownelsewhere, the phenomena should only be used as a canon for our understand-ing.
      </text>
     </text-unit>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0076"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0077"
         title="Quotation Marks"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>Quotation Marks
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0078"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0079"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>Quote test: “The paralogisms of practical reason are what first give rise to thearchitectonic of practical reason. ” and some more text. and ‘As will easily beshown in the next section, reason would thereby be made to contradict, in viewof these considerations, the Ideal of practical reason, yet the manifold dependson the phenomena. ’ even more.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0080"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0081"
         title="Simple Text-Generating Commands"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>Simple Text-Generating Commands
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0082"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0083"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>Some people use plain
        <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0084"
           actualtext="TeX"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>TEX
        </Span>
        <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>, but I prefer
        <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0085"
           actualtext="LaTeX"
           phoneme="[ˈlaːtɛx]"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>LATEX
        </Span>
        <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>instead.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0086"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0087"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>This page was produced May 20, 2016.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0088"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0089"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="2" ?>If nominated ..., I will not serve.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0090"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0091"
         title="Emphasizing Text"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Emphasizing Text
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0092"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0093"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
        <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0094"
           actualtext="LaTeX"
           phoneme="[ˈlaːtɛx]"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>LATEX
        </Span>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>offers
        <Em xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0095"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>one command
        </Em>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>and one declaration for emphasis.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0096"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0097"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
        <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
           id="ID.0098"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>\emph
        </Code>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>is done inlatex-lab-text, but how to handle
        <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
           id="ID.0099"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>\em
        </Code>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>is unclear as itcan go over paragraphs.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0100"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0101"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>strong aka bold face is mapped to/Strong, but here too it is unclear howto handle the switch.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0102"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0103"
         title="Preventing Line Breaks"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Preventing Line Breaks
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0104"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0105"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Anything to do here? If so, what for Mr. Jones and Figure 7
       </text>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0106"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0107"
         title="Footnotes"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Footnotes
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0108"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0109"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Footnotes
        <footnotemark xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0110"
           rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           referenced-as="2"
          >
          <?References objects="1" ?>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
         <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
            id="ID.0111"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextPosition="Sup"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>1
         </Span>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
        </footnotemark>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
        <footnote xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0112"
           rolemaps-to="FENote"
           referenced-as="1"
          >
          <?References objects="2" ?>
         <footnotelabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0115"
            rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
          <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
             id="ID.0116"
             xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
             Layout:TextPosition="Sup"
            >
           <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>1
          </Span>
          <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
         </footnotelabel>
         <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0113"
            rolemaps-to="Part"
           >
          <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
             id="ID.0114"
             xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
             Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
             rolemaps-to="P"
            >
           <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
           <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
           <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Like this one
           <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
          </text>
         </text-unit>
        </footnote>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>should be fine, as well as simple footnote marks
        <footnotemark xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0117"
           rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           referenced-as="4"
          >
          <?References objects="3" ?>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
         <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
            id="ID.0118"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextPosition="Sup"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>2
         </Span>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
        </footnotemark>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>with the text beingsupplied later.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
      <footnote xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0119"
         rolemaps-to="FENote"
         referenced-as="3"
        >
        <?References objects="4" ?>
       <footnotelabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0122"
          rolemaps-to="Lbl"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
        <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0123"
           xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
           Layout:TextPosition="Sup"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>2
        </Span>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
       </footnotelabel>
       <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0120"
          rolemaps-to="Part"
         >
        <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0121"
           xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
           Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
           rolemaps-to="P"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>The one for the mark. For good measure have a second paragraph.
        </text>
       </text-unit>
       <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0124"
          rolemaps-to="Part"
         >
        <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0125"
           xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
           Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
           rolemaps-to="P"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Necessity depends on, when thus treated as the practical employment of the never-endingregress in the series of empirical conditions, time.
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>
        </text>
       </text-unit>
      </footnote>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0126"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0127"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Question is: is this placed correctly?
       </text>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0128"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0129"
         title="Formulas"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Formulas
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0130"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0131"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>They should be fine too (and tested elsewhere). But here are the cases coveredin this section of the manual:
        <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0132"
           title="math"
           af="tag-AFfile1.tex"
           xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
           Layout:Placement="Inline"
          >
          <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile1.tex" xmlns="">
          $a+b$
          </AssociatedFile>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>a +b
        </Formula>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>is a short formula,
        <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0133"
           title="math"
           af="tag-AFfile2.tex"
           xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
           Layout:Placement="Inline"
          >
          <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile2.tex" xmlns="">
          $x$
          </AssociatedFile>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>x
        </Formula>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>is a variable and onecan use a math environment:
        <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0134"
           title="math"
           af="tag-AFfile3.tex"
           xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
           Layout:Placement="Inline"
          >
          <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile3.tex" xmlns="">
          $a-b$
          </AssociatedFile>
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>a−b
        </Formula>
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>though this is seldom done.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
    </Sect>
    <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
       id="ID.0135"
      >
     <subsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
        id="ID.0136"
        title="The Document"
        rolemaps-to="H3"
       >
      <section-number xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0137"
         rolemaps-to="Span"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>2.2.2
      </section-number>
      <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>The Document
     </subsection>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0138"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0139"
         title="The Title ``Page''"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>The Title “Page”
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0140"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0141"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>The title is tested at the beginning of the document. What of it needs furtherstructure?
       </text>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
    </Sect>
    <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
       id="ID.0142"
      >
     <subsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
        id="ID.0143"
        title="Sectioning"
        rolemaps-to="H3"
       >
      <section-number xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0144"
         rolemaps-to="Span"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>2.2.3
      </section-number>
      <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Sectioning
     </subsection>
     <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0145"
        rolemaps-to="Part"
       >
      <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0146"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
         rolemaps-to="P"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>In this document we can in theory test all sectioning commands other than
       <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
          id="ID.0147"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>\chapter
       </Code>
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>, but this is best done elsewhere, to keep the heading setup of this testin sync with the
       <Span xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
          id="ID.0148"
          actualtext="LaTeX"
          phoneme="[ˈlaːtɛx]"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>LATEX
       </Span>
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Manual.
      </text>
     </text-unit>
    </Sect>
    <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
       id="ID.0149"
      >
     <subsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
        id="ID.0150"
        title="Displayed Material"
        rolemaps-to="H3"
       >
      <section-number xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0151"
         rolemaps-to="Span"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>2.2.4
      </section-number>
      <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>Displayed Material
     </subsection>
     <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
        id="ID.0152"
        rolemaps-to="Part"
       >
      <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0153"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
         rolemaps-to="P"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>An example of a display quotation.
      </text>
      <quote xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0154"
         rolemaps-to="BlockQuote"
        >
       <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0155"
          rolemaps-to="Part"
         >
        <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0156"
           xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
           Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
           rolemaps-to="P"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>... it’s a good idea to make your input file as easy to read as possible.
        </text>
       </text-unit>
      </quote>
      <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0157"
         xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
         Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
         rolemaps-to="P"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="3" ?>I should be indented on both sides.
      </text>
     </text-unit>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0158"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0159"
         title="Quotation"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Quotation
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0160"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0161"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Quotations with several paragraphs. As any dedicated reader can clearly see,the Ideal of practical reason is a representation of, as far as I know, the thingsin themselves; as I have shown elsewhere, the phenomena should only be usedas a canon for our understanding.
       </text>
       <quote xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0162"
          rolemaps-to="BlockQuote"
         >
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0163"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0164"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Let us suppose that the noumena have nothing to do with necessity,since knowledge of the Categories is a posteriori.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0165"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0166"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Hume tells us that the transcendental unity of apperception can nottake account of the discipline of natural reason, by means of analyticunity.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0167"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0168"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>It remains a mystery why the Ideal stands in need of reason.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
       </quote>
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0169"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>And now the same with thequotation environment:
       </text>
       <quotation xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0170"
          rolemaps-to="BlockQuote"
         >
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0171"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0172"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Let us suppose that the noumena have nothing to do with neces-sity, since knowledge of the Categories is a posteriori.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0173"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0174"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Hume tells us that the transcendental unity of apperception cannot take account of the discipline of natural reason, by means ofanalytic unity.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0175"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0176"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>It remains a mystery why the Ideal stands in need of reason.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
       </quotation>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0177"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0178"
         title="Lists"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Lists
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0179"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0180"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Lists come in three basic flavors,itemize,enumerate, anddescription. Hereis an example of nested lists.
       </text>
       <itemize xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0181"
          xmlns:List="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/List"
          List:ListNumbering="Unordered"
          rolemaps-to="L"
         >
        <item xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0182"
           rolemaps-to="LI"
          >
         <itemlabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0183"
            rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>•
         </itemlabel>
         <itembody xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0184"
            rolemaps-to="LBody"
           >
          <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
             id="ID.0185"
             rolemaps-to="Part"
            >
           <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
              id="ID.0186"
              xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
              Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
              rolemaps-to="P"
             >
            <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>As any dedicated reader can clearly see, the Ideal of practical reason isa representation of, as far as I know, the things in themselves; as I haveshown elsewhere, the phenomena should only be used as a canon for ourunderstanding.
           </text>
          </text-unit>
         </itembody>
        </item>
        <item xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0187"
           rolemaps-to="LI"
          >
         <itemlabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0188"
            rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>•
         </itemlabel>
         <itembody xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0189"
            rolemaps-to="LBody"
           >
          <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
             id="ID.0190"
             rolemaps-to="Part"
            >
           <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
              id="ID.0191"
              xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
              Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
              rolemaps-to="P"
             >
            <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>They can be nested:
           </text>
           <enumerate xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
              id="ID.0192"
              xmlns:List="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/List"
              List:ListNumbering="Ordered"
              rolemaps-to="L"
             >
            <item xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
               id="ID.0193"
               rolemaps-to="LI"
              >
             <itemlabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                id="ID.0194"
                rolemaps-to="Lbl"
               >
              <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>1.
             </itemlabel>
             <itembody xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                id="ID.0195"
                rolemaps-to="LBody"
               >
              <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                 id="ID.0196"
                 rolemaps-to="Part"
                >
               <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                  id="ID.0197"
                  xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
                  Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
                  rolemaps-to="P"
                 >
                <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>The paralogisms of practical reason are what first give rise to thearchitectonic of practical reason.
               </text>
              </text-unit>
             </itembody>
            </item>
            <item xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
               id="ID.0198"
               rolemaps-to="LI"
              >
             <itemlabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                id="ID.0199"
                rolemaps-to="Lbl"
               >
              <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>2.
             </itemlabel>
             <itembody xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                id="ID.0200"
                rolemaps-to="LBody"
               >
              <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                 id="ID.0201"
                 rolemaps-to="Part"
                >
               <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
                  id="ID.0202"
                  xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
                  Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
                  rolemaps-to="P"
                 >
                <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>As will easily be shown in the next section, reason would therebybe made to contradict, in view of these considerations, the Ideal ofpractical reason, yet the manifold depends on the phenomena.
               </text>
              </text-unit>
             </itembody>
            </item>
           </enumerate>
          </text-unit>
         </itembody>
        </item>
        <item xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0203"
           rolemaps-to="LI"
          >
         <itemlabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0204"
            rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>•
         </itemlabel>
         <itembody xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0205"
            rolemaps-to="LBody"
           >
          <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
             id="ID.0206"
             rolemaps-to="Part"
            >
           <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
              id="ID.0207"
              xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
              Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
              rolemaps-to="P"
             >
            <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Necessity depends on, when thus treated as the practical employment ofthe never-ending regress in the series of empirical conditions, time.
           </text>
          </text-unit>
         </itembody>
        </item>
       </itemize>
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0208"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Some text directly following the list.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0209"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0210"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Here is an example of adescription list:
       </text>
       <description xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0211"
          xmlns:List="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/List"
          List:ListNumbering="Description"
          rolemaps-to="L"
         >
        <item xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0212"
           rolemaps-to="LI"
          >
         <itemlabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0213"
            rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>Term A
         </itemlabel>
         <itembody xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0214"
            rolemaps-to="LBody"
           >
          <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
             id="ID.0215"
             rolemaps-to="Part"
            >
           <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
              id="ID.0216"
              xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
              Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
              rolemaps-to="P"
             >
            <?MarkedContent page="4" ?>As any dedicated reader can clearly see, the Ideal of practical reasonis a representation of, as far as I know, the things in themselves; as I haveshown elsewhere, the phenomena should only be used as a canon for ourunderstanding.
           </text>
          </text-unit>
         </itembody>
        </item>
        <item xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0217"
           rolemaps-to="LI"
          >
         <itemlabel xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0218"
            rolemaps-to="Lbl"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>Term B
         </itemlabel>
         <itembody xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0219"
            rolemaps-to="LBody"
           >
          <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
             id="ID.0220"
             rolemaps-to="Part"
            >
           <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
              id="ID.0221"
              xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
              Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
              rolemaps-to="P"
             >
            <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>The paralogisms of practical reason are what first give rise to thearchitectonic of practical reason.
           </text>
          </text-unit>
         </itembody>
        </item>
       </description>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0222"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0223"
         title="Poetry"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>Poetry
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0224"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0225"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>An example ofverse.
       </text>
      </text-unit>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0226"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <quote xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0227"
          rolemaps-to="BlockQuote"
         >
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0228"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0229"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>There is an environment for verse
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0230"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0231"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>Whole features some poets will curse.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0232"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0233"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>For instead of making
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0234"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0235"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>Them do
          <Em xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
             id="ID.0236"
            >
           <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>all
          </Em>
          <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>the line breaking,
         </text>
        </text-unit>
        <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
           id="ID.0237"
           rolemaps-to="Part"
          >
         <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
            id="ID.0238"
            xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
            Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
            rolemaps-to="P"
           >
          <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>It allows them to put too many words on a line when they’d ratherbe forced to be terse.
         </text>
        </text-unit>
       </quote>
      </text-unit>
     </Sect>
     <Sect xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
        id="ID.0239"
       >
      <subsubsection xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/book"
         id="ID.0240"
         title="Displayed equation"
         rolemaps-to="H4"
        >
       <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>Displayed equation
      </subsubsection>
      <text-unit xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
         id="ID.0241"
         rolemaps-to="Part"
        >
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0242"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>Basic environments are
        <Code xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn"
           id="ID.0243"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>\[...\]
        </Code>
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>andequation, e.g.,
       </text>
       <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
          id="ID.0244"
          title="equation*"
          af="tag-AFfile4.tex"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:Placement="Block"
         >
         <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile4.tex" xmlns="">
         \begin {equation*}x' + y^2 = z_i^2\end {equation*}
         </AssociatedFile>
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>x′+y2=z2i
       </Formula>
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0245"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>and
       </text>
       <Formula xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
          id="ID.0246"
          title="equation"
          af="tag-AFfile5.tex"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:Placement="Block"
         >
         <AssociatedFile name="tag-AFfile5.tex" xmlns="">
         \begin {equation}x' + y^2 = z_i^2\end {equation}
         </AssociatedFile>
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>x′+y2=z2i
        <Lbl xmlns="http://iso.org/pdf2/ssn"
           id="ID.0247"
          >
         <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>(2.1)
        </Lbl>
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>
       </Formula>
       <text xmlns="https://www.latex-project.org/ns/dflt"
          id="ID.0248"
          xmlns:Layout="http://iso.org/pdf/ssn/Layout"
          Layout:TextAlign="Justify"
          rolemaps-to="P"
         >
        <?MarkedContent page="5" ?>also supported are all of theamsmath environments.
       </text>
